fields.physical_description:
1. box lid; sliding type with a raised edge along one long side. Both sides have been covered with chromolithographed labels. The under side is marked COPYRIGHT and shows the storage arrangement for the blocks in the box. It is printed in cream, black, reddish brown and blue. The top left corner and side have been torn away, also the top right corner. The label on the front shows 6 buildings, building blocks and scrolls. The titles are in German, English and French - RUDOLSTADTER
STEINBAUKASTEN, STONE BUILDING BOX and BOITE DE CONSTRUCTION. It is signed K QUARCK 987 (it is possible that the name is Quarek).  In the centre bottom is MADE IN GERMANY. Along the bottom edge on the left is SILBERNE MEDAILLE LEIPZIG 1897 and FIRST PRICE LONDON 1891 (price should read Prize). 

*There is considerable doubt as to whether the set is a Richter as many others were made in imitation. Although Richter did use the title Steinbaukasten it usually had ANKER in front and there are none of the normal trademarks, anchors or squirrels on the box. Likewise although
the blocks look the same, the patterning of many is very decorative. One firm may have been Gebr. Keller of Rudolstadt which used  RUDOLSTADTER STEINBAUKASTEN in its address though the only record of a mark is DIAMANT, 1903. 

2. box base; plain wood; there is the remains of a label on one side
`ecorirt' probably decorirt 
*3+. pieces of reconstituted stone; in various shapes, sizes and colours; most bear some form of pattern on at least one side rather than
being completely flat sided.
